			<meta property="og:description" content="Harvard Business School Professor Teresa Amabile compares much of work life to running on a treadmill.  People try to keep up with the demands of meetings, email, interruptions, deadlines, all while trying to be more productive and creative, she says, yet on many days they seem to make no progress at all, especially in creative endeavors. Amabile suggests the answer is to do less."/>
      
